  "summary": "Baron Lothair Rottschläger informs Anthony McGrath that restoration efforts in Hesslovakia have resumed following the death of Nicholas IV. The Baron states that the Hesslovian royal court supports Prince Michael's ascension to the throne, a move backed by the British government. However, the Baron warns Anthony that his presence is problematic because the memoirs of the late Count Stapleton contain secrets that could cause European chaos and spread damaging gossip regarding the Paulvich family. The Baron reveals that a weekly newspaper is prepared to publish these memoirs immediately upon their arrival. Despite the Baron offering Anthony increasing bribes, reaching two thousand pounds, to abandon his task, Anthony refuses, citing his honor and his commitment to the assignment.\n\nAfter the Baron departs, Anthony searches for a woman named Rueff. He discovers in a magazine that Mrs. Timothy Rue is actually Miss Virginia Gaussland, formerly Miss Rue. As Anthony prepares a package of letters, a menacing stranger enters his room and demands Stapleton's memoirs. The man identifies himself as a member of the Red Hand Party and presents a paper marked with a red hand symbol. When Anthony refuses to hand over the manuscript, the stranger threatens to shoot him. Anthony reacts by stepping forward and knocking the gun out of the man's hand.",
